Name: Cold Cut-out
Help: Desired cut-out temperature in coldest position/ set-point

Name: Warm Cut-out
Help: Desired cut-out temperature in warmest position/ set-point

Name: Temp Set Top
Help: In case of knob (potentiometer) failure, this setting would bring the temperature set-point to a particular desired position, between the warmest and coldest set-points, which could be set as the percentage between warmest (0%) and coldest(100%) positions/ set-points

Name: Compressor Differential
Help: Difference in the cut-in and cut-out temperartures at the coldest position (set-point)

Name: Min Runtime
Help: To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-outs, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor runs for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-out temperature.

Name: Alarm low function
Help: Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary deep temperatures."

Name: Alarm high function
Help:
"To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-ins, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor remains in idle state for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-in temperatures.

Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary warm temperatures.

Name: Cold Overtemp Alarm
Help: Enable or disable option for Alarm undertemp Function."

Name: Warm Overtemp Alarm
Help: Enable or disable option for Alarm overtemp Function.

Name: Cold Undertemp Alarm
Help: Warmest temperature allowed at the coldest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Warm Undertemp Alarm
Help: Warmest temperature allowed at the warmest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Alarm Delay
Help: Coldest temperature allowed at the coldest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Fan on during defrost
Help: Coldest temperature allowed at the warmest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Defrost Terminate Temperature
Help: Time delay to raise over or undertemperature alarm signal. It is not active at power up.

Name: Minimum Defrost Time
Help: Used in natural defrost method to accelerate the defrosting.

Name: Maximum Defrost Time
Help: Temperature at which the defrost session will be terminated.

Name: Minimum Defrost Interval
Help: Minimum time limit defined for defrost duration

Name: Fan Start Delay
Help: Maximum time limit defined for defrost duration

Name: Voltage Protect function
Help: Minimum time interval between two defrost sessions

Name: Minimum Cut-in Voltage
Help: Time delay to start the fan after compressor cut-in

Name: Maximum Cut-in Voltage
Help: The lowest voltage at which the compressor is allowed to Cut-in.

Name: Zero-Cross switching Function
Help: When voltage falls below the Minimum cut-in voltage, it waits until it reaches (MIV-VTR) after which it cuts-out the compressor. After this, the compressor would start again at Minimum Cut-in voltage (MIV) parameter.

Name: Zero-Cross Switchning
Help: This parameter will avoid sudden switching on and off of compressor due to voltage fluctuations.

Name: Remote Offset
Help: This cut-off voltage will override compressor minimum run time."

Name: Remote Deviation
Help: High voltage limit. If the voltage exceeds this limit, the compressor will turn off and is not allowed to start until the line voltage goes below this limit or minimum compressor stop time.

Name: Remote Sample Time
Help:
"
This parameter enhaces the relay life and also avoid relay sparks during relay on and off.This parameter is normally set to 0, which means, that the relay will be switched on and off when the line-voltage crosses zero. Hovewer, if you exactly know the power-factor of your load, you can adjust the switching time to compensate for that.

Name: Defrost temperature
Help: This parameter can be used to calibrate for sensor tolerances. It cancels the deviation caused by long lengths of sensor cable.

Name: Condenser temperature
Help: This parameter is used to compensate for bad sensor placement, to minimize the influence of the ambient temperature to the sensor.

Name: User set
Help: if RST parameter is set to zero, the temperature would be displayed immediately as it is read from the sensor.  If set to any other value for example 10, ETP R1 would sample the temperature every ten seconds and moving average of 20 samples would be calculated. So if there is a temperature change, the ETPR1 would take 20 multiplied by 10 seconds i.e., 200 Secs(Max) to reach the exact temperature.

Name: Control temperature
Help: Minimum run time of fan in order to avoid sudden ON/OFF of fan.

Name: Panel Spindle Selection
Enum: 0:Panel,1:Panel+Spindle with Stop Function,2:Panel + Spindle without stop function
Help: Minimum stop time of fan in order to avoid sudden ON/OFF of fan.

Name: Fan Min Run Time
Help: Difference in heater cut-in and cut-out temperartures.

Name: Fan Min Stop Time
Help: Difference in Fan Cut-in and cut-out temperatures.

Name: Heater Differential
Help: If set, the display will show the temperature in Fahrenheit.

Name: Operating mode
Help: In case of knob (potentiometer) failure, this setting would bring the temperature set-point to a particular desired position, between the warmest and coldest set-points, which could be set as the percentage between warmest (0%) and coldest(100%) positions/ set-points
